
[1]sabbatarian

   SABBATARIAN, n. [from sabbath.] One who observes the seventh day of the
   week as the sabbath, instead of the first. A sect of baptists are
   called sabbatarians. They maintain that the Jewish sabbath has not been
   abrogated.

   SABBATARIAN, a. Pertaining to those who keep Saturday, or the seventh
   day of the week, as the sabbath.
